-- Russia Equity Movers: Mechel, RusHydro, TNK-BP, VTB Bank
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-07-06T15:21:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-06/russia-equity-movers-rushydro-vtb-bank-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell for the
second day, losing 1.5 percent to 1,414.28 by the close in
Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index dropped 2.2 percent to
1,357.71.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Mechel (MTLR RX) dropped 1.4 percent to 207.60 rubles,
the second day of declines. Russia’s biggest coking coal
producer fell after saying work was temporarily halted at a mine
after the nation’s environmental regulator found violations.  OAO RusHydro (HYDR RX) declined 2.5 percent to 80.81
kopeks, the second day of losses. Russia’s largest hydropower
company fell a second day on a Kommersant report it may receive
a smaller-than-expected payment for selling a stake to state
holding company OAO Rosneftegaz.  TNK-BP (TNBP RX) jumped for the first time in three days,
adding as much as 3.3 percent, before trading up 0.3 percent to
76.25 rubles. AAR, a group representing billionaire partners in
the Russian oil producer, said it will offer to buy half of BP
Plc’s 50 percent holding within the next two weeks.  VTB Group (VTBR RX) dropped 3.8 percent to 5.62 kopeks, the
lowest level since June 28. Russia’s second-biggest lender
extended losses after posting a 13 percent first-quarter profit
drop yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
